abstract: A Broadway star on vacation reading, tweeting comedians and the authenticity of pizza.
snippet: A Broadway star on vacation reading, tweeting comedians and the authenticity of pizza.
lead_paragraph: Laura Benanti is a Tony Award-winning actress and singer who most recently appeared in the Broadway revival of “She Loves Me.” She has also had many roles on television, including stints on “Law and Order,” “Nashville” and now “Supergirl.”

abstract: The erstwhile Carrie Bradshaw celebrates her new show, a dark comedy about middle-age suburbanites and their crumbling marriage.
snippet: The erstwhile Carrie Bradshaw celebrates her new show, a dark comedy about middle-age suburbanites and their crumbling marriage.
lead_paragraph: There was Sarah Jessica Parker (“Sex and the City”) huddling with Matthew Broderick (“Election”), as guests tucked into plates of pumpkin agnolotti by Mario Batali (Babbo) and bantered about the latest Clinton White House run.

abstract: Shelagh Delaney’s play, once a hit in the West End and on Broadway, is revived by Pearl Theater Company.
snippet: Shelagh Delaney’s play, once a hit in the West End and on Broadway, is revived by Pearl Theater Company.
lead_paragraph: Shelagh Delaney was still a teenager when she sent her first script off to a London theater in 1958, enclosing a note that fairly bristled with a bold defensiveness.

abstract: Other restaurant openings include the John Lamb and Harold’s Meat & Three.
snippet: Other restaurant openings include the John Lamb and Harold’s Meat & Three.
lead_paragraph: MEGU New York once again has a branch of this lavish Japanese-style global restaurant chain, which closed its two Manhattan locations two years ago. The group is now owned by Jon Bakhshi, who also owns Beautique restaurant, a celebrity magnet, on West 58th Street. The sumptuous new Megu has replaced Cherry in the basement of the Dream Downtown hotel. A dramatic mirrored staircase leads to a lounge, a sushi bar and a vast dining room. Some of the décor, like a room decorated with antique kimonos, may be familiar to those who recall the original Megu in TriBeCa. Nothing is modest here, and that also goes for the menu, by the chef Frances Tariga-Weshnak, a native of the Philippines, who is serving spice-crusted duck, edamame lollipops with tahini sauce and Maine lobster with ginger emulsion. There’s an extensive selection of sushi. (Opens Thursday): 355 West 16th Street, 212-885-9400, meguworldwide.com.

abstract: This year’s honors speak to the additive nature of scientific research, with prizes recognizing people who built on the findings of others.
snippet: This year’s honors speak to the additive nature of scientific research, with prizes recognizing people who built on the findings of others.
lead_paragraph: The Lasker Awards, among the most respected prizes in medicine, will go to six researchers who made major discoveries in physiology and virology, and to a scientist who has tirelessly promoted science education, the Albert and Mary Lasker Foundation announced on Tuesday.
